node.text:
Maybe you have noticed or not, but  I’ve been super absent on here. So here’s a little update: Everyday I feel stronger and more balanced, and i’m making progress on my mental health with the GAPS diet (& now SSRI free). I feel like my true happy Joelle self is making a comeback. I made a few mistakes along the way, and if you have been here for a long time you know I’ve opened up a bit here and there about struggling with anxiety & depression throughout my life. Well, after 2 and a half years of being on SSRI medication I stopped gradually around this time last year (the medication seemed to not be working and it was making me tired and puffy). One thing I recommend is not getting off SSRIs like I did so fast, I should of tapered off of them over a year (I did this in 6 months and that was too short). I had insane withdrawals and I think that’s why I felt insanely depressed and not myself for so long. Have a plan and work with someone experienced that can help you get off of them safely. It’s different for everyone, and I feel like I need to do a YouTube video about this because there is sooo much to explain about it. Furthermore, in no way am I shaming anyone who is currently on them, they helped me so much in the first few years and I’d never want to sound like you should get off of them if you don’t want to or feel the need to. I am just speaking to the people who are curious about other options and ways to help their mental health. I know it’s a very sensitive topic and I have gotten some questions why I got off them, and I could go more into detail, as well as explain the diet I’m on that quite literally saved my life. In all cases, please talk to your healthcare professional if you are needing help with your medication and seek their advice first. I currently see a naturopath and she has been amazing and is so helpful. 🙏🏼 I will try to go into more detail about everything soon. 🤍
Photo by @wilderness_addict, edit by me

node.text:
I recently stumbled upon an old journal of mine from when I lived abroad in Switzerland. Seeing my written words, I was reminded of what sparked my passion for travel, photography, and writing. My time there opened my eyes to a new horizon in my life, and sparked a personal mission to pursue a career that allowed me to do what I love. 🌲 ⛺️
 
This last year made me lose sight of this horizon at times, but reading my old journal and getting back on the road more, is rejuvenating me and opening my eyes to new horizons to chase, discover and enjoy (perhaps with a glass of @hirschwhiskey?) once again. 🥃
 
How do you #ChaseYourHorizon?
 
#HIRSCHWhiskey #21+

node.text: Nothing beats that post hike feeling! 💦 Connecting with my body and adding movement to my day is so important for my mental health and overall wellbeing. Since the weather is getting much nicer, I’m excited to do more hikes wearing all my favorite @lululemon apparel. Here I’m wearing the Find Your Pace shorts 3in and Gloss Trim Run 1/2 Zip (which is now on sale), both are perfect for warmer weather hikes! 🏃🏼‍♀️ #thesweatlife #a d
